The term here translated 'spirit' is <i>substantia separata</i>, 'a 
substance existing by itself apart' from matter. The expression seems 
to be taken from the <b>aut&ecirc; kath ahut&ecirc;n ousia</b> of the 
Platonic Ideas, which the Neo-Platonists personified as spirits. 

